All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
ApiFactory
This class is a factory pattern implementation for creating instances based on the version of the ApiInterface.
Currently, only one version exists, so the getInstance() method only accepts the 'LAST' parameter.
If you want to use API of liblpu237, you have to create the instance of ApiInterface by ApiFactory.getInstance().
ApiFactory.VERSION
the definition of version string.
ApiInterface
All API class must be implement these interfaces.
API user have to use methods of this interface only.
Don't use a method of this interface implementer directly.
Lpu237Callback
this class is the abstract callback class of WaitMsrOriButtonWithCallback() in ApiInterface interface.
Lpu237Callback.Result
the result value of processing in Lpu237Callback, Lpu237GetSetCallback or Lpu237DoneCallback.
Lpu237Callback.TypeRx
the reading type of the current Lpu237Callback instance.
Lpu237DoneCallback
this class is the abstract callback class of ToolsMsrStartApplySetting() or ToolsMsrSetInterfaceToDeviceAndApply() in ApiInterface interface.
Lpu237GetSetCallback
this class is the abstract callback class of ToolsMsrStartGetSetting() and ToolsMsrStartSetSetting() in ApiInterface interface.
Lpu237Tags
pre/postfix key object class of lpu237
UsbDevHandle
usb device handle class of Our API this class contain device path and UsbDevice instance if android system.
